{"questionId":"3854986","questionHtml":"<p>Three lamps (X, Y and Z) are connected as shown in the circuit. The emf of the cell is 20 V. The internal resistance of the cell is negligible. The power dissipated by X, Y and Z is 10 W, 20 W and 20 W respectively.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/8c3860a09bcba4a70f0e39b682909322983a798c.png\"></p>\n<p>What is the voltage across Lamp X and Lamp Y?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width:346px;height:179px;border-color:#000000;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width:128.117px;height:29px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Lamp X</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:143.883px;height:29px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Lamp Y</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">A.</td>\n<td style=\"width:128.117px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">16 V</td>\n<td style=\"width:143.883px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">4 V</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:45px;\">B.</td>\n<td style=\"width:128.117px;text-align:center;\">4 V</td>\n<td style=\"width:143.883px;text-align:center;\">16 V</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">C.</td>\n<td style=\"width:128.117px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">4 V</td>\n<td style=\"width:143.883px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">8 V</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">D.</td>\n<td style=\"width:128.117px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">16 V</td>\n<td style=\"width:143.883px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">16 V</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3854986","referenceCode":"23M.1A.SL.TZ1.17","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Three lamps (X, Y and Z) are connected as shown in the circuit. The emf of the cell is 20 V. The internal resistance of the cell is negli